Amazing I take a weeks vacation and come back to 350 notes, and see this one.

  Both of your arguments are indeed accurate. 

  But it is an added bonus to the recipient or customer to hear their loved one&#39;s voice on tape rather that by word of mouth from a gifted clairaudient, clairvoyant, psychic person. That is the icing on the cake.

  What would bother me terribly is if any of us researchers received a message from a spirit in which we could actually make contact with their loved one to send the tape, and then to try and charge the contactee for the recording.  

  In my opinion if any of us receive such a message with that clarity, we should send/give it to the contactee free of charge as doing so is in a sense a spiritual gift from the spirit to the contactee, and we are just the messenger.  I have been researching this concept, and I myself hope to one day be able to receive clear and concise messages which would enable me to contact the spirit&#39;s loved one to give them that message should they wish to receive it. And I gurantee you it will be free of charge. 

  Have any of you received on any occasion enough info from the spirits to be able to contact the loved one and give them the recording?




Early Cuyler &lt;ecuyler@...&gt; wrote:
              How true it is.

Jeremy

