&lt;div&gt;Amazing I take a weeks vacation and come back to 350 notes, and see this one.&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div&gt;Both of your arguments are indeed accurate. &lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div&gt;But it is an added bonus to the recipient or customer to hear their loved one&#39;s voice on tape rather that by word of mouth from a&nbsp;gifted clairaudient, clairvoyant, psychic person. That is the icing on the cake.&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div&gt;What would bother me terribly is if any of us researchers received a message from a spirit in which we could actually make contact with their loved one to send the tape, and then to try and charge the contactee for the recording.&nbsp; &lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div&gt;In my opinion if any of us receive such a message with that clarity, we should send/give it to the contactee free of charge as doing so is in a sense a spiritual gift from the spirit to the contactee, and we are just the messenger.&nbsp; I have been researching this concept, and I
 myself hope to one day be able to receive clear and concise messages which would enable me to contact the spirit&#39;s loved one to give them that message should they wish to receive it. And I gurantee you it will be free of charge. &lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div&gt;Have any of you received on any occasion enough info from the spirits to be able to contact the loved one and give them the recording?&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;Early Cuyler &lt;ecuyler@...&gt;&lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt; wrote:&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;BLOCKQUOTE class=replbq style=&quot;PADDING-LEFT: 5px; MARGIN-LEFT: 5px; BORDER-LEFT: #1010ff 2px solid&quot;&gt;  &lt;DIV id=ygrp-text&gt;  &lt;div&gt;  &lt;DIV style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: times
 new roman, new york, times, serif&quot;&gt;  &lt;DIV style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman,new york,times,serif&quot;&gt;How true it is.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Jeremy&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;  &lt;DIV style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 12pt; BORDER-LEFT: rgb(16,16,255) 2px solid; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman,new york,times,serif&quot;&gt;----- Original Message ----&lt;BR&gt;From: Steve Hultay &lt;urkel23@aol.&lt;WBR&gt;com&gt;&lt;BR&gt;To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups&lt;WBR&gt;.com&lt;BR&gt;Sent: Sunday, April 6, 2008 7:53:35 AM&lt;BR&gt;Subject: [EVP-ITC] Re: boxes on ebay&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;  &lt;DIV id=ygrp-text&gt;  &lt;div&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Jeremy,&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;There will always be a market for less educated people and some to &lt;BR&gt;take advantage of that. There is a a saying out there---- &quot;Stupid &lt;BR&gt;people don&#39;t know they&#39;re stupid&quot;. How true is that.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;-Steve &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;--- In &lt;A href=&quot;mailto:EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&quot; target=_blank rel=nofollow ymailto=&quot;mailto:EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&quot;&gt;EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .com&lt;/A&gt;, Early Cuyler &lt;ecuyler@... &gt; wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; Margaret, I can&#39;t argue with what
 you&#39;ve said. I&#39;m just saying &lt;BR&gt;there are those who take advantage and should have no business in &lt;BR&gt;doing so. One example I can give is Chris Moon. He charges people &lt;BR&gt;to do box sessions. I can&#39;t remember the exact fee, but it&#39;s &lt;BR&gt;outrageous that he&#39;s doing this, not to mention, he does so with a &lt;BR&gt;Frank&#39;s box. He is a self proclaimed medium and I&#39;ve heard from many &lt;BR&gt;sources that he is nothing but a fake. &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; So I attribute my frustration with people of this type, but again I &lt;BR&gt;say, as long as there are people dumb enough to pay for this, then &lt;BR&gt;there will always be those who take advantage.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; Personally, I feel anyone who is gifted with mediumship or other &lt;BR&gt;advanced intuitive abilities should use it as a gift to help others, &lt;BR&gt;not for monetary gain.. I&#39;m not being judgmental here, that&#39;s just &lt;BR&gt;how I feel. I have a friend who is also a legitimate medium and I &lt;BR&gt;don&#39;t agree that she should use her abilities for gain,
 but it &lt;BR&gt;doesn&#39;t mean I like her any less. My not liking it won&#39;t change the &lt;BR&gt;fact that it happens, it&#39;s just the way things go. &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; Do I think that Ron is taking advantage of people? No I don&#39;t. &lt;BR&gt;Ron says he uses the best parts available and that the cost of the &lt;BR&gt;Minibox is very close to what it costs to manufacture it. How close, &lt;BR&gt;I have no idea. On the other hand, I don&#39;t own one as I think $399 &lt;BR&gt;or $449 for the &quot;crystal enhanced version,&quot; is a lot to pay for a &lt;BR&gt;device that, from what I&#39;ve heard, produces the same results as a &lt;BR&gt;Radio Shack radio for $25-$40. &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; Jeremy&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; ----- Original Message ----&lt;BR&gt;&gt; From: itcdeadpeople &lt;ITCdeadpeople@ ...&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; To: &lt;A href=&quot;mailto:EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&quot; target=_blank rel=nofollow ymailto=&quot;mailto:EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&quot;&gt;EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .com&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; Sent: Saturday, April 5, 2008 1:32:28 PM&lt;BR&gt;&gt; Subject: [EVP-ITC] Re: boxes on ebay&lt;BR&gt;&gt;
 &lt;BR&gt;&gt; Hi Jeremy. If everyone knew about these support &lt;BR&gt;boards and that other resources are &lt;BR&gt;&gt; available to them, that would be one thing. Obviously everyone &lt;BR&gt;here is aware of that. But &lt;BR&gt;&gt; not everyone knows this place exists. &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; And even if they do know about the boards here, how many would have &lt;BR&gt;the nerve to ask &lt;BR&gt;&gt; for help from strangers? As Bruce recently shared, he gives people &lt;BR&gt;invitations to contact &lt;BR&gt;&gt; him privately in case they are too shy just ask a question &lt;BR&gt;publicly. Which means, by the &lt;BR&gt;&gt; way, to some degree they have overcome some of that shyness in &lt;BR&gt;order to post whatever it &lt;BR&gt;&gt; was to begin with, which inspired him to make this offer. What if &lt;BR&gt;they don&#39;t even have the &lt;BR&gt;&gt; gumption to be anything more than be a look-i-loo?&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; I&#39;m guessing many people are just surfing the net, checking out &lt;BR&gt;paranormal stuff, and run &lt;BR&gt;&gt; across the hacked boxes for sale. &lt;BR&gt;&gt;
 &lt;BR&gt;&gt; Again, I ask people who are taking the position you and Bruce are &lt;BR&gt;regarding profits ... do &lt;BR&gt;&gt; you have this same harsh sentiment toward Ron Ricketts, who makes &lt;BR&gt;and sells the &lt;BR&gt;&gt; MiniBoxes? I realize he is passionate about this research and &lt;BR&gt;helping others. Does that &lt;BR&gt;&gt; give him amnesty for making a profit? &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; Personally I think we need to not be so judgmental. At what point &lt;BR&gt;does &quot;profitable gain in &lt;BR&gt;&gt; the paranormal field&quot; become &quot;sickening?&quot; I have a friend who is a &lt;BR&gt;medium. I mean THE &lt;BR&gt;&gt; REAL DEAL. He charges for his services. The fee is reasonable &lt;BR&gt;compared to many in his &lt;BR&gt;&gt; field. Does he do this because he&#39;s a terrible person looking to &lt;BR&gt;take advantage of people? &lt;BR&gt;&gt; NO, he does so because he has been given a gift that changes &lt;BR&gt;people&#39;s lives for the better. &lt;BR&gt;&gt; But he has to make a living.... has to support himself in some way. &lt;BR&gt;And because he has &lt;BR&gt;&gt; chosen to
 provide this service full time (and is not a trust fund &lt;BR&gt;baby), he makes a profit. &lt;BR&gt;&gt; This allows him to help far more people than he could if working &lt;BR&gt;some other kind of job &lt;BR&gt;&gt; and providing his services at no cost on the side. &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; I realize this is not exactly the same thing as gouging people on &lt;BR&gt;the price for a &lt;BR&gt;&gt; commercially available product, but making such blanket statements &lt;BR&gt;about profitability in &lt;BR&gt;&gt; the paranormal field being sickening is rather short-sighted, in my &lt;BR&gt;opinion. &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; I have a southern friend who likes to say, &quot;It&#39;s a mighty thin &lt;BR&gt;plank that ain&#39;t got two sides.&quot; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; I just don&#39;t think we have the right to claim that simply because &lt;BR&gt;someone is offering a &lt;BR&gt;&gt; good and or service for profit to consumers in the paranormal &lt;BR&gt;market, that this &lt;BR&gt;&gt; automatically means they are taking advantage of other&#39;s &lt;BR&gt;vulnerabilities. &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; For Pete&#39;s sake, no one is
 twisting the people&#39;s arms to buy those &lt;BR&gt;units on eBay. They are &lt;BR&gt;&gt; perfectly free to buy from whatever source they choose. Since the &lt;BR&gt;units do work as &lt;BR&gt;&gt; claimed, we can argue that people have overpaid, shopped unwisely, &lt;BR&gt;or whatever. I assure &lt;BR&gt;&gt; you this happens every single day throughout the retail market &lt;BR&gt;place with all types of &lt;BR&gt;&gt; products and services. &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; I will say I have a fairly heathy dose of distain for &lt;BR&gt;charlatans/scam artists (of any flavor in &lt;BR&gt;&gt; any field) but that is not what we are talking about here. We are &lt;BR&gt;talking about people who &lt;BR&gt;&gt; are offering legitimate products to consumers. I&#39;d rather see &lt;BR&gt;people doing this for profit, &lt;BR&gt;&gt; even when obscene, than running scams that damage people&#39;s &lt;BR&gt;physical, mental, and/or &lt;BR&gt;&gt; financial well-being. &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; Margaret&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; --- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .com, Early Cuyler &lt;ecuyler@ &gt; wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&gt;
 &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Very well put, Bruce. Profitable gain in the paranormal field is &lt;BR&gt;sickening.. Unfortunately, &lt;BR&gt;&gt; there are those who continue to support the ones profiting, so it &lt;BR&gt;will continue. It makes &lt;BR&gt;&gt; me sick that people take advantage of others vulnerabilities, &lt;BR&gt;especially when it comes to &lt;BR&gt;&gt; spiritual matters, but that&#39;s a rant for another time and place.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; If someone is afraid to try hacking a radio or lacks the proper &lt;BR&gt;tools, they are more than &lt;BR&gt;&gt; welcome to send them to me and I&#39;ll do it for them and ship it &lt;BR&gt;back. As Bruce said, it&#39;s not &lt;BR&gt;&gt; for recognition, but it&#39;s to help further the research. I wouldn&#39;t &lt;BR&gt;be doing this research if it &lt;BR&gt;&gt; wasn&#39;t for Frank, Bruce, Steve and the others who put in their time &lt;BR&gt;and effort. The &lt;BR&gt;&gt; possibilities are only limited by our willingness to work &lt;BR&gt;together. The more we work &lt;BR&gt;&gt; together, the better the communication will get.
 &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Jeremy&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; ----- Original Message ----&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; From: bruce halliday &lt;paranormalinvestig ating@ &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; To: evp-itc@yahoogroups .com&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Sent: Saturday, April 5, 2008 11:15:21 AM&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Subject: RE: [EVP-ITC] boxes on ebay&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Guy&#39;s&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Do not give in to these demons that are trying to make a buck &lt;BR&gt;from the research we love &lt;BR&gt;&gt; and the equipment we use.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; I have given away including the shipping 5 RS boxes for free, 4, &lt;BR&gt;470&#39;s and 1 469 all &lt;BR&gt;&gt; hacked by me.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; I did not do it to gain popularity or even wanted a thank you. my &lt;BR&gt;sole motivation was to &lt;BR&gt;&gt; bring new people into the research and &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; in turn change someones life and perpetuate the idea of strength &lt;BR&gt;in numbers, in this &lt;BR&gt;&gt; case strength of
 communication.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; To all new people on this board, do not patronise these wolves &lt;BR&gt;that prey on the needs &lt;BR&gt;&gt; and wants of others. &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; The RS 20 -125 is everything the 470 &amp; 469 are and a little more. &lt;BR&gt;do not let the size or &lt;BR&gt;&gt; complicated button arrangement scare you off.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; the hack is as simple as the others. &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Do not buy any RS hacks from ebay, they are sold with the wrong &lt;BR&gt;energy attached to &lt;BR&gt;&gt; them, spirit wise.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; That is why I and all other researchers should follow the example &lt;BR&gt;of a great man to &lt;BR&gt;&gt; whom we owe all of this research.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Mr. Frank Sumption, who was in a position at one time to make a &lt;BR&gt;substantial amount of &lt;BR&gt;&gt; money from his boxes and&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; was offered the opportunity on a silver platter. But chose to &lt;BR&gt;follow what had been asked &lt;BR&gt;&gt; of him by higher entities.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; And that was to keep the
